adband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-640x388.png" alt="" width="640" height="388" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-640x388.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-600x364.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-768x465.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-1536x931.png 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-2048x1241.png 2048w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.16.33-1200x727.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> iOS 15 will boast redesigned notifications, which includes the addition of app logos and contact profile pictures. Users will also be able to get a notification summary scheduled to show according to their preferences. New focus modes will offer more settings – including work, personal, and sleep – for iOS to better control notifications and contacts so that you can stay focused or relaxed, based on your needs. This mode will be shared with contacts so that they are aware of your current situation. iOS 15 will also suggest apps and contacts that would fit into a certain focus category. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-400649" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.20.58-640x356.png" alt="" width="640" height="356" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.20.58-640x356.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.20.58-600x333.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot