.02-640x356.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.22.02-600x334.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.22.02-768x427.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.22.02-1536x854.png 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.22.02-2048x1139.png 2048w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.22.02-1200x667.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-400657" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-640x351.png" alt="" width="640" height="351" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-640x351.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-600x329.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-768x421.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-1536x842.png 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-2048x1123.png 2048w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.23.33-1200x658.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> A new feature in Photos dubbed Memories can use machine learning to collect photos into relevant galleries or animations and add matching music from Apple Music. The latter will analyse photos and adjust music to make personalised recommendations which also incorporates a user’s own library and curated playlists. Apple wants to make users fully independent of a physical wallet with further features added to its payments platform Apple Wallet. This includes more support for digital house and accommodation keys. Apple will also support digitising US ID documents — like drivers’ licences — and saving them on their wallet. This can then be used as a valid form of identification in participating states in the country and will be integrated into Transportation Security Administration systems at US airports. New Apple Maps details will include items like turn lanes, cross-walks, bus-lanes and robots, as well as live 3D interchange rendering. Coming to select cities, users will be able to scan buildings when they are lost, allowing Maps to identify their location and navigate them towards their destination. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-400663" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-640x358.png" alt="" width="640" height="358" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-640x358.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-600x335.png 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-768x429.png 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-1536x859.png 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-2048x1145.png 2048w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-06-07-at-19.32.59-1200x671.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> iOS 15 will also bring a new feature called Conversation Boost to AirPods. This will help callers to better understand who they are talking to in a busy environment. Users will also be able to adjust ambient background noise levels. In addition, Apple’s smart assistant Siri will be able to announce important notifications. Lastly, Apple’s Safari browser has also been updated to be more consistent across devices. The browser has been redesigned with new features which include tab grouping and tab bookmarking. Support for extensions has also been added to the browser app on iPhone and iPad.